sixth, the summer after my sixth, between my fifth and sixth grade, when Ray Palmer, I believe that was his name, editor of Flying Saucers Magazine, in a store in London, Wisconsin, and his childhood friend who ran the store, came back from Roswell with a stretch about a yard long. And it was, it was woven. It wasn't a thin strip of metal. It was like they took nylon fibers, but it wasn't nylon. It was ceramic.

2108
01:38:15,200 --> 01:38:34,560
And wound it. And then when you flowed, shined the flashlight through it, the light would bend without being absorbed. Now, you, but before you do it for the craft, you first have to know about the particles, because you have to know how to build the fiber optics before you can do anything else.

2109
01:38:34,560 --> 01:38:48,700
So Roswell, you mentioned the Roswell Grays, and you're talking about the Roswell Craft. The lore is that it made its way to Wright-Patterson, Wright-Airfield at the time. And did you think, you're saying it eventually made its way to Area 51 or to the Nevada test range?

2110
01:38:48,900 --> 01:38:56,560
I don't know where it made its way to, but I don't care, because I've seen the real one and I know what it looks like. According to just, according to that...

2111
01:38:56,560 --> 01:38:59,100
Where did you see it? Did you see it in Nevada?

2112
01:38:59,500 --> 01:39:16,180
In Nevada. I've seen a craft of that type many times. On one, as I describe in my book on the Valleys of the Grace, on one cold and snowy night in the fall back in the 60s, when I damn near died in the fog,

2113
01:39:16,180 --> 01:39:32,220
and the scout craft with the young lady in it and some of her friends, accompanied by the deep space craft and the teenage craft, they had gone down to the bend in the road.

2114
01:39:32,560 --> 01:39:37,960
And she alone, she was just learning to run the craft, so they didn't let her take it up in the air.

2115
01:39:38,760 --> 01:39:45,420
And before the fog moved in, when I was walking down there, I was on the side of a hill, I was alone.

2116
01:39:45,420 --> 01:39:50,240
And she had brought the craft in on the paved, on the gravel road.

2117
01:39:50,900 --> 01:39:56,740
She just had the control coils running, and she had opened up the door on the side.

2118
01:39:57,120 --> 01:40:04,460
I was very reluctant to approach a craft because I knew from experience that they all have those fields surrounding them.

2119
01:40:04,920 --> 01:40:08,780
And then if you get too close, it's like walking into the back of a jet engine.

2120
01:40:08,780 --> 01:40:17,120
And when the Jinda engine is running, you've got to just stay and let them see you and let them come as close as they want, or you'll get your ass burned.

2121
01:40:17,660 --> 01:40:20,860
So I wasn't—but she had powered down the outer coils.

2122
01:40:21,480 --> 01:40:30,060
So from her point of view, there was nothing keeping me from just walking the final distance and stepping up into the craft and saying hi,

2123
01:40:30,060 --> 01:40:34,040
and meeting her and the others who were on the craft.

2124
01:40:34,660 --> 01:40:44,640
I didn't realize at the time that the teenager who was the backup pilot, he was a young gray.

2125
01:40:45,860 --> 01:40:48,720
They looked just like someone from Mongolia.

2126
01:40:49,500 --> 01:40:54,100
But the other three, she and the other three, were actually humans.

2127
01:40:54,100 --> 01:41:02,880
They were young Chinese people that the Gray's had rescued, not abducted, but they had been orphaned and the Gray's had reputed.

2128
01:41:03,420 --> 01:41:08,760
And the whole point was that they were trying to return them to human society.

2129
01:41:09,720 --> 01:41:16,700
But first, you ought to find a human who everybody trusts, including the children.

2130
01:41:17,360 --> 01:41:23,720
And the human has to be somebody who trusts them in return, and the human they had figured that,

2131
01:41:24,100 --> 01:41:29,360
they had chosen, had this last name Hall and the first name Charlie, okay?

2132
01:41:29,680 --> 01:41:30,780
They're Charles, right?

2133
01:41:31,660 --> 01:41:33,400
And you say, well, why didn't they tell me?

2134
01:41:33,420 --> 01:41:37,700
And they say, well, that's why we picked him, because he'll figure it out if we just give him time, right?

2135
01:41:38,520 --> 01:41:40,760
Why tell him early and scare him, right?

2136
01:41:40,960 --> 01:41:47,280
You know, that's why we picked him, because he's perfect at convergent, divergent reasoning, and he'll figure it out.

2137
01:41:48,180 --> 01:41:51,180
And that's what they're doing, waiting for me to come.

2138
01:41:51,180 --> 01:41:58,360
And what they had was the very same craft of the three that crashed at Roswell.

2139
01:41:58,900 --> 01:42:00,960
What they had was the very same craft.

2140
01:42:01,280 --> 01:42:03,180
And in the back of that craft...

2141
01:42:04,200 --> 01:42:07,120
Do you think we know how to fly these crafts now?

2142
01:42:07,500 --> 01:42:09,160
Do you think humans know how to fly them?

2143
01:42:09,280 --> 01:42:11,320
I'll finish this sentence and I'll answer it.

2144
01:42:11,320 --> 01:42:15,040
In the back of that craft was a restroom.

2145
01:42:16,080 --> 01:42:22,480
In the back of all those people are real physical biological entities.

2146
01:42:23,180 --> 01:42:24,720
They all have to eat.

2147
01:42:24,860 --> 01:42:26,780
They all have to breathe air, drink water.

2148
01:42:27,160 --> 01:42:30,660
And they all have to periodically go to the restroom.

2149
01:42:30,660 --> 01:42:37,160
And therefore, every craft in the back has a bathroom, you see?

2150
01:42:37,660 --> 01:42:47,200
And therefore, when you say, like the crash at Kingman, the young lady that survived, the sheriff there,

2151
01:42:47,340 --> 01:42:53,440
said that after she came out and they were waiting for help to come, what did she do?

2152
01:42:53,440 --> 01:42:58,620
So, in his own words, he said she went back in the craft and stayed in the back.

2153
01:42:59,420 --> 01:43:04,100
And the UFO people say it must be a shrine where she was praying.

2154
01:43:05,360 --> 01:43:10,580
And, of course, I think that's really laughable because having seen the craft, there's no shrine back there.

2155
01:43:10,640 --> 01:43:12,020
What there is is a bathroom.

2156
01:43:13,000 --> 01:43:16,680
And there's also food storage.

2157
01:43:16,680 --> 01:43:23,240
And so, if the craft has crashed and she's got to wait a while, like every other biological entity,

2158
01:43:23,420 --> 01:43:26,520
they're going to fall back on the bathroom, you see?

2159
01:43:26,740 --> 01:43:30,480
There's no reason to fall back on the control panels because the craft isn't running.

2160
01:43:30,680 --> 01:43:32,600
That's why they crashed, see?

2161
01:43:33,000 --> 01:43:35,320
But the UFO people all have this thing.

2162
01:43:35,580 --> 01:43:41,260
Well, there was a time they said in all those crafts, there must be a shrine in the back, you know, where they go and pray.

2163
01:43:41,500 --> 01:43:44,480
And you'd say, no, no, no, no, I've seen the craft.

2164
01:43:44,480 --> 01:43:46,220
They're going, that's a bathroom, right?

2165
01:43:47,080 --> 01:43:50,320
And I have a whole class of stories in that vein.

2166
01:43:51,400 --> 01:43:56,520
And so, when I say my advantages that I've been there and seen that,

2167
01:43:56,520 --> 01:44:08,280
I say the wreckage that was sitting in the hangar at Roswell that was recovered from Roswell.

2168
01:44:08,620 --> 01:44:10,920
When you say, what was that like?

2169
01:44:11,080 --> 01:44:16,080
Well, that wreckage had the bathroom on the other side.

2170
01:44:16,940 --> 01:44:23,500
And so, that meant for the part that blew in was blowing in on the food storage, you see?

2171
01:44:24,020 --> 01:44:32,320
And so, when you went on the wreckage of that, I would guess that you would find on the other side what remained of the restroom,

2172
01:44:32,440 --> 01:44:34,120
which might not be very much.

2173
01:44:34,120 --> 01:44:40,160
I'm saying when you, okay, but now in answer to your, what was your question that you wanted me to answer?

2174
01:44:40,160 --> 01:44:44,840
I asked if humans, you mentioned that these, there were these Chinese occupants of the craft.

2175
01:44:44,840 --> 01:44:49,800
Do you think that humans can fly these exotic, you know, ET crafts?

2176
01:44:49,800 --> 01:44:56,460
It's like everything else if they're trained, okay?

2177
01:44:56,820 --> 01:45:03,160
It's like if they have an opportunity to learn, if they have a trainer.

2178
01:45:03,160 --> 01:45:16,280
Yeah, it's not something you can do naturally for the same reason that a Cessna airplane, they tell me it's a pretty simple airplane to fly.

2179
01:45:16,280 --> 01:45:23,060
Okay, I've actually flown one as co-pilot for about 45 minutes, but not by myself.

2180
01:45:23,060 --> 01:45:28,880
There was a trained pilot, I was in the co-pilot seat, and the trained pilot was in the pilot seat.

2181
01:45:28,880 --> 01:45:36,640
And it was a nice night, and all I was doing was flying straight and level and saying, yeah, I'm not moving anything, okay, if you call that flying.

2182
01:45:37,460 --> 01:45:42,300
Well, does the training involve the mind-matter connection?

2183
01:45:43,000 --> 01:45:45,800
There are rumors that there are no control panels.

2184
01:45:46,040 --> 01:45:49,080
Do you sort of psychically connect with the craft?

2185
01:45:50,160 --> 01:45:52,140
You don't do anything psychically.

2186
01:45:52,560 --> 01:45:54,800
Everything is electronics.

2187
01:45:54,800 --> 01:46:11,800
The electronics either are adjusted to tell what you're thinking and therefore react because you're thinking, or to not work at all.

2188
01:46:12,580 --> 01:46:16,880
It isn't the person that has to change their way of thinking.

2189
01:46:16,880 --> 01:46:23,560
It's the person who's adjusting the electronics has to adjust it.

2190
01:46:24,100 --> 01:46:26,380
It's unique for each human.

2191
01:46:27,300 --> 01:46:33,540
So how many of these tall whites were out there with you, if you had to guess or estimate?

2192
01:46:34,580 --> 01:46:38,740
It varied with how many ships were in port.

2193
01:46:38,740 --> 01:46:49,960
See, the deep spaceships would arrive and would come and go on schedule the same way an airport is.

2194
01:46:50,660 --> 01:46:56,180
They liked to come and go near the night of the full moon.

2195
01:46:56,880 --> 01:47:02,260
And on the night of the full moon, the moon and the earth and the sun all form a line.

2196
01:47:02,260 --> 01:47:11,640
And so behind the earth in its orbit is a uniform gravitational field and it's going away from the incoming craft.

2197
01:47:12,000 --> 01:47:15,680
So if anything goes wrong, they can back off and the earth won't run into them.

2198
01:47:15,780 --> 01:47:16,320
It'll go away.

2199
01:47:16,820 --> 01:47:23,180
This is much different than the Norwegians with 24 teeth who want to come in on the front side of the earth

2200
01:47:23,180 --> 01:47:31,840
because the Norwegians with 24 teeth, with less technology, must land at any price, even if the earth runs into them.

2201
01:47:32,460 --> 01:47:40,080
But the grays and the tall whites, the deep spacecraft of the tall whites, want to come in on the night of the full moon.

2202
01:47:40,540 --> 01:47:43,960
The grays, who have a base on the moon, come and go at any time they want.

2203
01:47:44,700 --> 01:47:52,680
The tall whites, the craft come on schedule and they have different schedules.

2204
01:47:53,000 --> 01:47:55,420
Some are making a two-month schedule.

2205
01:47:55,420 --> 01:48:00,440
So the longest schedule I saw was craft that take five years.

2206
01:48:01,140 --> 01:48:08,440
And those craft with a five-year schedule, I was told, were coming directly from their home planet.

2207
01:48:08,440 --> 01:48:18,220
Of course, since all the craft travel many times faster than the speed of light, I'm not sure where their home planet was.

2208
01:48:18,220 --> 01:48:31,800
But if there were no craft in port, then the number of tall whites at the base wasn't particularly large.

2209
01:48:31,800 --> 01:48:46,380
I'm not sure what the number was, but it would be rare to see as many as a hundred out in the desert if there were no ships in deep spacecraft in port.

2210
01:48:46,380 --> 01:48:58,900
On the other hand, the night that Pamela was supposed to pass her test to head up a tall white technology transfer team,

2211
01:48:58,900 --> 01:49:14,060
by dressing up and disguising herself as a human woman and the other tall white by dressing up and disguising himself as a human man specifically named Charlie Hall.

2212
01:49:14,280 --> 01:49:26,380
And she would specifically pretend to be his wife so they could go into places like Livermore and pretend to be humans and talk to the scientists, I'm guessing.

2213
01:49:26,580 --> 01:49:28,660
Wait, explain what you just said.

2214
01:49:28,900 --> 01:49:30,940
In a minute.

2215
01:49:31,680 --> 01:49:33,240
The night she was going to pass that—

2216
01:49:33,240 --> 01:49:34,760
Are you saying that you're a tall white?

2217
01:49:35,200 --> 01:49:36,180
No, I'm not a tall white.

2218
01:49:36,220 --> 01:49:37,560
I was born in Brooklyn, Wisconsin.

2219
01:49:37,700 --> 01:49:38,960
My parents all came from England.

2220
01:49:38,960 --> 01:49:43,120
Well, then, but they mimicked you.

2221
01:49:43,240 --> 01:49:48,200
One of the tall whites disguised themselves as you and your wife and then showed up at Livermore Labs?

2222
01:49:49,340 --> 01:49:50,200
I'm guessing.

2223
01:49:51,040 --> 01:49:51,660
I'm guessing.

2224
01:49:52,140 --> 01:49:53,340
And how do you know?

2225
01:49:53,580 --> 01:49:55,020
Well, where did that come from?

2226
01:49:55,300 --> 01:49:57,500
I've never seen any classified documents.

2227
01:49:57,500 --> 01:50:02,460
I'm guessing only from my personal experience talking with the tall whites.

2228
01:50:03,320 --> 01:50:13,420
They've told you that they kind of used you for inspiration to infiltrate—or not infiltrate, maybe that's too aggressive a word, but to enter American scientific programs.

2229
01:50:13,420 --> 01:50:17,240
I'm just totally guessing.

2230
01:50:17,240 --> 01:50:19,240
But the night she was—

2231
01:50:19,240 --> 01:50:27,400
He told them how to not be afraid around humans and to act easily when in the presence of humans.

2232
01:50:27,400 --> 01:50:41,760
That was his whole MO, that he was supposed to be there, because they were as terrified of us as we might have been terrified by them.

2233
01:50:42,280 --> 01:50:46,140
And it was—that was what the program was.

2234
01:50:46,140 --> 01:50:58,100
On that night, there were more tall white scout craft located up the valley and on the eastern side of Indian Springs Valley.

2235
01:50:58,240 --> 01:50:58,880
On what night?

2236
01:50:58,880 --> 01:51:19,100
The night that Pamela was supposed to pass her final exam, the crowd that formed of tall whites and a few human generals and bigwigs on the eastern side of the valley, there were more than I could count.

2237
01:51:19,100 --> 01:51:25,920
I stopped counting at 35, but I guessed there were at least 70 there.

2238
01:51:26,400 --> 01:51:36,580
There were so many scout craft and tall whites that that whole side of the valley was white, fluorescent white people, scout craft.

2239
01:51:37,060 --> 01:51:39,140
It looked like a county fair over there.

2240
01:51:39,140 --> 01:51:51,360
And all they were going to do is watch her, Pamela, while the teacher and Pamela, over where the ammunition bunker was at three and a half miles,

2241
01:51:51,960 --> 01:52:05,600
was to watch her, the teacher and Pamela, walk down the paved pathway or one-lane road from the ammunition bunker on the east side

2242
01:52:05,600 --> 01:52:13,300
down to about halfway, down to about halfway, where there was a ridge, and then the teacher would wait there.

2243
01:52:13,980 --> 01:52:29,880
And then Pamela, with all of her technology turned off, okay, on totally trusting that I'm a nice guy to be around, okay,

2244
01:52:29,880 --> 01:52:43,140
otherwise totally helpless against me if I'm not, was supposed to continue walking down the pathway until she got to the range boards.

2245
01:52:43,400 --> 01:52:49,840
And then while I was working, while I had released the balloon and I was tracking the balloon,

2246
01:52:50,520 --> 01:52:56,820
to just walk over to me disguised as a human.

2247
01:52:56,820 --> 01:53:03,060
She didn't have to be disguised as a human lady, just wearing her natural suit, totally turned off,

2248
01:53:03,520 --> 01:53:06,520
to just walk over to me, the way you and I are.

2249
01:53:07,100 --> 01:53:14,020
And then while I was working, walk around behind me and turn her back to me,

2250
01:53:14,760 --> 01:53:20,440
proving that she trusted me, just like the scene from The Man Called Horse,

2251
01:53:20,440 --> 01:53:31,180
where the Indian Chief does that to Horse, turn her on and talk to me with her back turned towards me,

2252
01:53:31,280 --> 01:53:36,700
totally turned off for everything, and then walk around to the others with everybody watching,

2253
01:53:37,640 --> 01:53:39,100
and then walk around and say,

2254
01:53:39,100 --> 01:53:44,960
hey, it's been so nice to meet you, Charlie, and then go on, and then she could then leave.

2255
01:53:46,100 --> 01:53:54,020
And her husband, the guy pretending to be me as her husband, would then have to do it next, okay?

2256
01:53:54,900 --> 01:53:57,880
On that night, she failed the test.

2257
01:53:57,960 --> 01:54:03,420
On that night, she panicked and got about, well, she didn't even get down to the quarter-mile limit,

2258
01:54:03,800 --> 01:54:09,720
when she panicked and was afraid that I was truly an ugly monster, that she couldn't trust and ran off.

2259
01:54:10,240 --> 01:54:15,300
But there came a night when she had to do that, and that's described in my book.

2260
01:54:15,300 --> 01:54:18,640
What do you think the Tall Whites want with humanity?

2261
01:54:19,140 --> 01:54:25,340
Do you think they have goals for us, or do you think they're just trying to engage in diplomatic relations?

2262
01:54:27,300 --> 01:54:35,180
Well, they came here in the middle of the last ice age because we, for the same reason that we have a base on Guam,

2263
01:54:35,940 --> 01:54:44,060
the sun and the solar system exists in the middle of a huge void in space.

2264
01:54:44,060 --> 01:54:52,160
The next closest star, Alpha Centauri, or Proxima Centauri, is almost four light-years away.

2265
01:54:53,240 --> 01:55:01,580
Most stars, or many stars, have another star within two light weeks, okay?

2266
01:55:01,760 --> 01:55:07,500
It's not all unusual for many stars to be not more than a light-year apart.

2267
01:55:07,500 --> 01:55:18,200
But if you're going to cross that big void in space as you're conducting interstellar commerce for your own good,

2268
01:55:18,600 --> 01:55:21,180
then it's nice to have a place in the middle,

2269
01:55:21,560 --> 01:55:26,700
because that void is therefore something like eight or ten light-years across,

2270
01:55:27,720 --> 01:55:30,880
or six or eight, a big long light-years.

2271
01:55:30,880 --> 01:55:37,680
And it's nice to have a place in the middle where you can stop and get food and water,

2272
01:55:38,580 --> 01:55:44,800
go outside your spacecraft and repair it, where you can stop and rest,

2273
01:55:45,420 --> 01:55:50,240
but also get minerals or other things that you might need.

2274
01:55:50,320 --> 01:55:51,180
So it's a pit stop.

2275
01:55:51,560 --> 01:55:52,700
It's a pit stop.

2276
01:55:52,940 --> 01:55:53,280
Interesting.

2277
01:55:53,280 --> 01:55:57,440
And, of course, the reason that there are many of their spacecraft doing that

2278
01:55:57,440 --> 01:56:04,820
is because there's only—it's for the same reason that there are many Air Force planes that stop at Guam,

2279
01:56:05,180 --> 01:56:07,720
because location, location, location.

2280
01:56:08,060 --> 01:56:09,060
What do you make of—

2281
01:56:09,060 --> 01:56:16,260
If you're there, it's a big help if you have some locals who grow some food for you,

2282
01:56:16,320 --> 01:56:19,520
they're plant-eaters, the Toloites, as the Greys are,

2283
01:56:20,140 --> 01:56:23,560
and do the work of harvesting and hand you the food.

2284
01:56:23,560 --> 01:56:32,040
What do you make of rumors, stories, that Ike Eisenhower, you know, meeting possibly, you know,

2285
01:56:32,160 --> 01:56:37,260
Palm Springs, 1954, this treaty, you know, you say five crafts showed up.

2286
01:56:37,260 --> 01:56:43,020
There's another story, you know, Hallman Air Force Base, where there's a landing

2287
01:56:43,020 --> 01:56:47,840
and there's a possible interaction between, you know, some generals on the base

2288
01:56:47,840 --> 01:56:55,460
and these tall beings, but they seem to actually have, like, almost pharaonic Egyptian headdress.

2289
01:56:56,100 --> 01:57:00,860
And this video, I think, was promised at one point to Rod Serling and Bob Emenager,

2290
01:57:01,060 --> 01:57:02,920
who made UFOs Past, Present, and Future.

2291
01:57:02,920 --> 01:57:05,700
And the video never came.

2292
01:57:06,220 --> 01:57:11,160
But I've spoken to, you know, some pretty interesting people in the UFO whistleblower world

2293
01:57:11,160 --> 01:57:16,340
who do stand by that account, that that was like a real meeting.

2294
01:57:16,480 --> 01:57:17,820
Do you think that that happened?

2295
01:57:18,840 --> 01:57:23,280
And was it a tall white that came out of the craft at Hallman Air Force Base?

2296
01:57:23,280 --> 01:57:31,860
I'll maintain my policy of never commenting on other people's stories.

2297
01:57:32,860 --> 01:57:41,080
And the reason is because my books are based totally on my own experience.

2298
01:57:41,340 --> 01:57:41,540
Yep.

2299
01:57:41,540 --> 01:57:50,540
And it's not based on anything I've read or any—they're not based on any classified material.

2300
01:57:50,680 --> 01:57:52,380
I was never part of any project.

2301
01:57:53,000 --> 01:57:57,160
They're based on what—when you say, what was life for me?

2302
01:57:57,420 --> 01:57:57,660
Yeah.

2303
01:57:57,660 --> 01:58:04,740
And what I'm trying to do in my books, one of the major things I'm trying to do in my books,

2304
